CM ============================================================
CM Arcanum Reference Deck — 3-Element Yagi-Uda
CM V-REAL-002 in docs/nec-import/validation.md
CM ============================================================
CM Classic 3-element Yagi-Uda: reflector, driven element, director.
CM Tests multi-wire parsing, tag uniqueness, and source referencing
CM across a more complex geometry than the half-wave dipole.
CM
CM Geometry:
CM   Frequency:    300 MHz  (lambda = 1.0 m)
CM   Elements along x-axis (horizontal, perpendicular to boom)
CM   Boom along z-axis
CM   Wire radius:  0.001 m (all elements)
CM   9 segments per element
CM
CM Element dimensions (from classical 3-element Yagi design tables):
CM   Reflector:      0.500 m total (0.250 m each side)  at z =  0.00 m
CM   Driven element: 0.473 m total (0.2365 m each side) at z =  0.25 m
CM   Director:       0.440 m total (0.220 m each side)  at z =  0.56 m
CM
CM Spacings:
CM   Reflector  -> Driven:   0.25 m (lambda/4)
CM   Driven     -> Director: 0.31 m (0.31 lambda)
CM
CM Source:
CM   Delta-gap voltage source on driven element (tag 2, segment 5)
CM   Segment 5 is the center of a 9-segment element
CM
CM Expected results (Phase 3/4):
CM   Single main beam in forward direction (+z, toward director)
CM   Front-to-back ratio > 10 dB
CM   Gain approximately 7-8 dBd (9-10 dBi)
CM   Input impedance: approximately 20-30 + j0 Ω near resonance
CM   (driven element slightly short of resonance by design)
CM
CM Pass criterion for V-REAL-002:
CM   3 wires parsed, correct segment counts, source on tag 2 only,
CM   all tags unique and correctly mapped in tag registry.
CM
CM Provenance: Synthesized by ORI for Arcanum validation.
CM   Dimensions from classical Yagi design tables (Kraus, Antennas).
CM   Compatible with NEC-2 and EZNEC for cross-validation.
CE
CM ============================================================
CM GEOMETRY
CM ============================================================
CM Tag 1: Reflector — 0.500 m total, at z = 0.00 m
GW 1 9 -0.250 0.0 0.00 0.250 0.0 0.00 0.001
CM Tag 2: Driven element — 0.473 m total, at z = 0.25 m
GW 2 9 -0.2365 0.0 0.25 0.2365 0.0 0.25 0.001
CM Tag 3: Director — 0.440 m total, at z = 0.56 m
GW 3 9 -0.220 0.0 0.56 0.220 0.0 0.56 0.001
GE 0
CM ============================================================
CM SIMULATION PARAMETERS
CM ============================================================
CM Delta-gap voltage source on driven element (tag 2, segment 5)
EX 0 2 5 0 1.0 0.0
CM
CM Frequency: 300 MHz
FR 0 1 0 0 299.792458 0.0
CM
CM Frequency sweep 200-400 MHz to observe bandwidth (uncomment to use)
CM FR 0 21 0 0 200.0 10.0
CM
CM Far-field radiation pattern, 5 degree grid
RP 0 37 73 1000 0.0 0.0 5.0 5.0 0.0
CM
EN
